#
# ============================================================================
# BEHAVIORS
#
# 1. PostgreSQL Wire Protocol Compliance
#    - Implements full PostgreSQL startup message sequence
#    - Supports both simple and extended query protocol
#    - Parameter binding (prevents SQL injection)
#    - Binary data handling (CopyIn/Out)
#    - Row and result descriptions
#    - Transaction management (begin/commit/rollback)
#    - Error handling and recovery
#
#
# 2. Connection Pool Management
#    - LIFO queue for reusing connections
#    - Min connections (default: 2, max: 10)
#    - Connection health checks
#    - Automatic reconnection on failure
#
#
# 3. Query Performance
#    - Prepared statements with parameter caching
#    - Bulk operations support
#    - Result streaming for large datasets
# #
# 4. Migration Support
#    - Versioned schema migrations
#    - Rollback on failure
#    - Migration history tracking
# #
# IMPORTS
#
# Use postgres wire protocol definitions from src/tri/postgres_wire_protocol.zig
# Use std.crypto for SCRAM-SHA256 authentication (via MD5 password)
# Use zig-golden-float kernel database patterns as reference
# ============================================================================
